Class Streamable.DefaultImpls

  • norswap.violin.stream.Streamable.DefaultImpls
  • Enclosing interface:
    Streamable<T>

    public static class Streamable.DefaultImpls

    A streamable is an object that can yield or be represented as a interface Stream.

    See Also:
    interface Stream

      static java.util.Iterator<T> iterator(Streamable<? extends T> $this)

    • Method Detail

      • iterator

        public static java.util.Iterator<T> iterator(Streamable<? extends T> $this)

        Returns an iterator backed by a stream.

        This method is required in order to be able to use interface Streamable instances in Kotlin for loops. This is why it is not an extension method (to make for loops available without the need to import extension methods).

        See Also:
        interface Streamable
